    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">How does the dual licensing system affect regular players?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Most players cannot distinguish between PIGO and e-Games platforms. A 2025 survey found that 78% of active online gaming participants could not identify which license type their preferred platform held. Both license types require PAGCOR compliance and offer player protection mechanisms, though PIGO operators face stricter AML and identity verification requirements. The primary risk for players is that regulatory confusion makes it harder to distinguish licensed platforms from unlicensed ones.</div>
